## What is the current behavior?

Inside my application, since Angular 11.2.6, I have the following issue on one of the form:
1. Remove FormGroup B from inside a FormGroup A
2. Re-Add the same FormGroup B inside the FormGroup A
3. Repeat `1.` and `2.` 
4. Use `FormGroup.reset(..)` to set FormGroup B values
5. FormControl inside FormGroup B are empty inside the DOM
6. If I click inside one of FormGroup B FormControl, then I click outside, I get the following error:
    `There is no FormControl instance attached to form control element with path: 'individual -> first'` 

The code look like that:
```ts
export class AppComponent {
  form: FormGroup;
  subform: FormGroup;
  constructor() {
    this.subform = new FormGroup({titi: new FormControl('')});
    this.form = new FormGroup({});
    this.subform.reset({titi: "Hello 1"});
    this.form.addControl('subform', this.subform);
    this.form.removeControl('subform');
    this.subform.reset({titi: "Hello 2"});
    this.form.addControl('subform', this.subform);
    this.form.removeControl('subform');
    this.subform.reset({titi: "Hello 3"});
    this.form.addControl('subform', this.subform);
  }
}
```
But I have to be clear: I wasn't able to reproduce it in a new project or Plunkr, only inside my app, so there is something more going on that I haven't find.

## What is the new behavior?

FormControl inside FormGroup B have correct values (set by `FormGroup.reset(..)`)

## Does this PR introduce a breaking change?

I don't think so.

## Other information

I have found that the issue started with the following commit:
https://github.com/angular/angular/commit/60ac9643334b83b6b720afd1b7d7fadf02c4e7fc

I don't think my PR should be merged like that, I'm just sharing my finding, in case someone can help me, or in case someone has the same issue.

